Evaluation :

Confusion Matrix: Predicted vs Actual values ground truth 
TP , TN , FP , FN

If we get more FP , FN then we try wit hdifferent models and get the best model with least values of FP and FN

Accuracy : TP+TN / (TP + TN + FP + FN) : Correct predictions / Total Predictions

Recall : TP / (TP + FN) , out of all postive values , how many are actually predicted positives?

Precision:  TP / (TP + FP)  , among all positive predictions how many are actual positives ? 

Potential problem : We have high accuracy , but have very low values for recall and precision

F1 score: We need a metric which considers both precision and recall for evaluation a model 
A harmonic mean of precision and recall is the F1 score.

This score tells how the model acutally performed


How do we come up with the treshold value?
ROC Curve ( Receiver Operator Charteristics): it represents various confusion matrices for various thresholds
Curve for Sensitivity vs 1-specificity
Precision = Specificity

FP rate : 1- specificity

a point where TP is high and FP is low will be a threshold value

AUC ( Area Under Curve): Which model covers the maxnimum area , that is considered a best model
We take roc curves of all the models and check which modles curve covers the max area.

Which model to choose? Plot AUC curve and the model which cover more area is the best model.

